The UK and Italy commit to use their CoP26 presidency to work with Kenya to drive climate action.Kenya took proactive measures to reduce emissions, vulnerability and enhance resilience. On December 12, 2015, the 21st Conference of the Parties to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (COP21) resulted in the first universal climate agreement in Paris-Le Bourget under the French presidency. On that day, 195 countries and the European Union succeeded, after 13 days of hard negotiations, in putting collective interests ahead of national interests and adopting a historic agreement – the Paris Accord.



