More countries are committing and raising their national ambitions — popularly known as Nationally Determined Contributions (NDC) — to reduce emissions by 2030 in order to align the commitments with a trajectory compatible with the 2C and efforts towards 1.5C goal.
Sustainable economies
For most, the concept of carbon neutrality in the second half of the century is within reach. At a critical moment when the world is fighting the Covid-19 pandemic and we’re being pushed towards rebuilding more sustainable economies, it is of paramount importance to collectively raise our ambition and reignite the spirit of the Paris Agreement.



